    "In Digital Realty Trust v. Somers (2018), the Supreme Court unanimously held that Dodd-Frank's anti-retaliation protection covers only employees who report to the SEC, because the statute defines a whistleblower that way. Employees who report only internally must rely on Sarbanes-Oxley instead. Choosing the channel is therefore a legal as well as a practical decision, and the two regimes carry different deadlines and remedies.",
